12/09/2003
DOBOJ, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- On Thursday (11 September), SFOR representatives held discussions with the army chiefs of Republika Srpska (RS) and the BiH Federation concerning defence reforms. Deputy Chief of General Staff of the RS Army General Stamenko Novakovic said the talks focused on preparations for next week's session of the Joint Military Commission, which will address the optimal number of armed forces personnel. He confirmed the army had completed work on a draft restructuring plan. Other participants, including BiH Federation Army Chief of General Staff Atif Dudakovic, told reporters the meeting also tackled military infrastructure and the sale of excess equipment. (SRNA, BBC - 11/09/03)
